    <item>
      <title>Re: Cleric Aura's (Level 70 is a waste of time)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11087#M11087</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Guard effects, like the one on the aura, don't stack but rather take the highest effect similar to how haste or run speed works.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I'm actually changing this aura slightly, though, along with most other auras.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;As the auras were built, they recast their effects every 6 seconds on&amp;nbsp;everyone&amp;nbsp;in range, sort of like a bard playing a song.&amp;nbsp; Auras (all Spheres of Influence, really) are just areas within the game world that can apply an effect on a player when they enter it and remove it when they leave it.&amp;nbsp; Because of this, recasting the effects every few seconds isn't necessary in most cases and just adds unnecessary&amp;nbsp;load on the servers.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;I've changed almost all the auras to be like normal spheres now where the effect stays on a player&amp;nbsp;for as long as they are in range of the aura.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;That led to a particular problem with the cleric ones since it would cause the effect to go away after it had absorbed the max damage&amp;nbsp;and then you'd have to leave the area and return for it to reapply it.&amp;nbsp; To fix that, I've completely removed the damage cap on the ability so as long as you are in range of the aura, you'll simply take less damage from melee attacks.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;I've slightly reduced the amount of absorption to compensate for it being always on&amp;nbsp;and I've changed the spells so the level 70 version is more powerful than the level 55 one.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This is still in testing, but barring any unforseen problems, should go out with the patch next week.&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/FONT&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rashere&lt;/FONT&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Wed, 08 Mar 2006 19:54:21 GMT</pubDate>
