      <title>Re: Cleric Aura's (Level 70 is a waste of time)</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=clericbalance&amp;message.id=11132#M11132</link>
      <description>&lt;blockquote&gt;&lt;hr&gt;Rashere wrote:&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;Guard effects, like the one on the aura, don't stack but rather take the highest effect similar to how haste or run speed works.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;I'm actually changing this aura slightly, though, along with most other auras.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;As the auras were built, they recast their effects every 6 seconds on everyone in range, sort of like a bard playing a song.  Auras (all Spheres of Influence, really) are just areas within the game world that can apply an effect on a player when they enter it and remove it when they leave it.  Because of this, recasting the effects every few seconds isn't necessary in most cases and just adds unnecessary load on the servers.  I've changed almost all the auras to be like normal spheres now where the effect stays on a player for as long as they are in range of the aura. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;That led to a particular problem with the cleric ones since it would cause the effect to go away after it had absorbed the max damage and then you'd have to leave the area and return for it to reapply it.  To fix that, I've completely removed the damage cap on the ability so as long as you are in range of the aura, you'll simply take less damage from melee attacks.  I've slightly reduced the amount of absorption to compensate for it being always on and I've changed the spells so the level 70 version is more powerful than the level 55 one.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;This is still in testing, but barring any unforseen problems, should go out with the patch next week.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;div&gt;Rashere&lt;/div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Thanks,&lt;br&gt;This answers my orginal question and concern. 5 precent is a good number for the level 70 version. Its something that players can see but yet not be overly powerful. Anything less will be difficult for players to judge. For normal groups this is one of my favorate auras.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;I do think the Vie spell line should hang in there a little longer. Most normal group mobs hit me for 1k so it normally lasts 17 hits.</description>
